h2: ['In numbers, India is only consistently behind the US, Russia and Brazil. It has invariably overtaken other hotspots of Covid-19 over the past few days in reporting fresh cases every 24 hours.']

title: Coronavirus LIVE Updates: Rajasthan reports 48 fresh cases, 2 deaths - India Today
h1: ['Coronavirus LIVE Updates: Rajasthan reports 48 fresh cases, 2 deaths']
h2:
['09:50 AM IST: The government of Tamil Nadu on Friday permitted the reopening of beauty parlours and salons across the state from tomorrow (Sunday). The state has not permitted salons and parlours to be opened in Chennai and the coronavirus containment zones. The state government has announced that no AC will be allowed in these shops and they can be open from 7 am to 7 pm.', "09:43 AM IST: Rajasthan reported 48 fresh positive cases of coronavirus till 9 am on Saturday morning. The state's number of deaths has also climbed by two, taking it to 155. The total number of positive cases in Rajasthan has now surged to 6,542, while active cases have hiked to 2,695, the state's health department said.", "09:13 AM IST: BREAKING: India has recorded the highest one-day spike in the number of its coronavirus cases. In the past 24 hours, India has recorded a total of 6654 new Covid-19 cases. With the new number of cases, India's count has now climbed to 1.25 lakh.", '08:47 AM IST: 32 more cases were reported in Nepal on Saturday morning, taking the total number of cases in the country to 548, the Nepal health ministry has said.', '08:45 AM IST: All the passengers coming to J&K by air/rail will be kept in institutional quarantine for 14 days and will be tested for Covid-19 using the RTPCR test. If tested negative they will be sent home otherwise to a hospital. This is the UT protocol under the Disaster Mgt Act: J&K government', '08:33 AM IST: China on Friday reported no new cases of the novel coronavirus. This is the first time that China reported no new cases of the infection since the pandemic began in the central city of Wuhan late last year.', '08:28 AM IST: The United States, in the past 24 hours, has reported a total of 1260 deaths. With the new number of deaths due to the coronavirus infection, the toll in the country has mounted to 95,921, according to Johns Hopkins University.', '08:07 AM IST: The Indian Council of Medical Research (ICMR) on Friday okayed the use of hydroxychloroquine (HCQ) for the healthcare and frontline workers as a preventive medication involved in coronavirus infection-related activities.
The premier health research body recommended the use of HCQ for asymptomatic healthcare workers working in non-Covid-19 hospitals and the frontline staff on surveillance duty in containment zones.
The Lancet, a premier medical journal, has, however, found that those being treated with HCQ and chloroquine are at a higher risk of death and irregular heart rhythms.
We will be updating live on coronavirus situation from across the world, stay with us.', " Coronavirus LIVE Updates: The number of coronavirus positive cases in India on Friday surpassed the 1.18 lakh mark as more infections were reported from across the country. On Thursday, India reported the highest single-day spike in the past 24 hours beginning Wednesday. According to the official data, India reported a total of 6,088 new Covid-19 cases. With over 6,000 cases, India's total number of Covid-19 tally mounted to 118,447. Delhi, too, reported its highest single-day spike in coronavirus cases. Including the new Covid-19 cases, Delhi's total number of coronavirus cases climbed to 12,319. Meanwhile, China reported 39 new coronavirus cases, including 35 asymptomatic infections from Covid-19 epicenter, Wuhan. The global coronavirus tally, according to Johns Hopkins University, has mounted to 5,210,065. More than 338,142 people have died due to the Covid-19 infection. IndiaToday.in would be running live news updates on coronavirus from across the world, stay with us."]
